						               													<description>Ortho is a game where players form words from letters on cards. The Ortho deck has 52 cards, each with a letter at either end; the two letters may be the same or different, and if different the player chooses which letter is used. There are also two &amp;quot;Chief&amp;quot; cards that are wild and can stand for any letter.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players start with seven cards each. In a turn a player draws the top of the deck or discard pile, and if possible either plays a word onto the table, or adds cards to a word on the table to make another word. In either case a word of 2 letters scores 1 point, and doubling for each additional letter (e.g. 3 letters 2 points, 4 letters 4 points, 5 letters 8 points, etc.). 32 points is the maximum allowed for any word.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The hand ends when a player uses all their cards in play, calling &amp;quot;Ortho!&amp;quot; and also earning from each player one point per card left in their hand.  (Presumably a hand also ends when the deck is gone.) A player wins by either Ortho'ing with a total of 104+ points, or ending a hand with 128+ points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
